records.addlTxt:
Defendant Stephen D King in court with attorney Cheryl Anne Ward.  
Kimberly Dorice Schoepp for DeAnn Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Amended Information filed.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Information, waived its reading.  

Charge amended to:

COUNT 1:  OBSTRUCTING/RESISTING AN OFFICER, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 946.41(1), 939.51(3)(a),  a Class  A Misdemeanor
COUNT 2:  DISORDERLY CONDUCT, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1), 939.51(3)(b), a Class B Misdemeanor

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS AMENDED COUNTS 1 AND 2:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, straight time with credit for 0 days.  No Electronic Monitoring.
COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to Count 1, straight time, with credit for 0 days.  No Electronic Monitoring.

The Court STAYED these sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 MONTHS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
* Count 1 ONLY: Serve 45 days in the House of Correction, straight time, no good time- STAYED for use at agent discretion;
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens;
*No driving without valid WI drivers license or occupational license (as authorized);
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in job/vocational training;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking Intervention counseling;
*Participate in Parenting counseling;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*As to both counts: pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of probation period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  

Appeal rights given. Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
